Some tests may have very long messages passed to junit Assert or Exception causes. Unlimited UI component sizes can cause problems, e.g the X server can freeze while moving the mouse over the test window when it renders the tree node overlay at full length.

Limit is set to all environments to simplify code, infinite length one-liners have questionable use anyway.

The full msg is always visible when the tree node is expanded in its formatted form (including line breaks).

Code cleanup: some warnings were dealt with


test:
```java
    @Test
    public void veryLongMsg() {
        throw new RuntimeException("Nein!\n".repeat(500)+"ENDE");
    }
```
